    pearls: ["TXA is TIME-CRITICAL: give within 1 hour for maximum benefit, still effective up to 3 hours, HARMFUL after 3 hours", "TXA preserves existing clots: it does NOT form new clots. It prevents premature fibrinolysis of hemostatic clots already formed at the bleeding site.", "Do NOT wait for TEG/ROTEM to show fibrinolysis: by the time lab results return, the 3-hour window may close. Administer empirically for significant hemorrhage.", "CRASH-2 trial: TXA reduced all-cause mortality in traumatic hemorrhage. Greatest benefit when given within 1 hour (RR 0.87).", "TXA costs less than $5 per dose: it is one of the most cost-effective interventions in hemorrhage management", "GI bleeding is NOT an indication for TXA: HALT-IT trial showed no benefit and possible harm in GI hemorrhage"],
